            <p class="q"> What is Saffron? </p>
            <p class="a"> Saffron delivers freshly cooked meals to your home.</p>
            <p class="q"> What is the difference between Saffron and other food delivery services? </p>
            <p class="a"> Saffron provides gourmet food delivery with a personal touch. With Saffron, you get the quality of a restaurant meal, right to your door. Our chefs prepare meals with heart, using fresh, high-quality ingredients.</p>
            <p class="q"> How fresh is your food?</p>
            <p class="a"> We prepare all of our gourmet meals fresh daily, right in our kitchens. Each meal includes a signed card from the chef.</p>
            <p class="q"> When can I place an order? </p>
            <p class="a"> You can place an order any time, any day! Every meal has a different cut-off time to get delivery, so be sure to check the website for the cut-off time on the day youâ€™re placing your order.For Shabbos meals, we recommend ordering no later than Thursday at 12:00 PM. For weekday meals, we recommend ordering no later than one hour prior to the delivery window.</p>
            <p class="q"> What should I do if my order hasn't arrived? </p>
            <p class="a"> If your order hasn't arrived, send us an email at <a href="mailto:support@saffronpremiumeats.com">support@saffronpremiumeats&shy;.com</a> and we'll get it sorted out for you right away.</p>
            <p class="q"> Can I send a meal as a gift?</p>
            <p class="a"> Yes! When you place your order, just choose the "Gift" option at checkout and we'll send your recipient a gift card with your special message.</p>
            <p class="q"> Are the meals kosher?</p>
            <p class="a"> All meals ordered from Saffron are certified kosher by Rabbi Yechiel Steinmetz.</p>
            <p class="q"> Where do you deliver?</p>
            <p class="a"> Saffron is currently delivering to customers in Monsey, NY. We might deliver to other places in the future, so keep us in mind!</p>
            <p class="q"> What kinds of meals can I order?</p>
            <p class="a"> You can order a wide variety of meals, including personal and family lunch, dinner and shabbos packages. As well as catering services for your simcha or corporate events.</p>
            <p class="q"> How do I pick up my order?</p>
            <p class="a"> If you've ordered for pickup, just come to the side-rear entrance of 51 Main St. Monsey, NY.</p>
            <p class="q"> Which package should I order?</p>
            <p class="a"> The Classic Packages are our most affordable meals, with the Premium Packages being higher quality and more expensive.</p>
            <p class="q"> Are any of your meals dairy?</p>
            <p class="a"> No. All of our meals are categorized as meat according to kosher tradition.</p>
            <p class="q"> What kinds of gift cards do you have?</p>
            <p class="a"> We have gift cards for every occasion! You can also order a one-time meal for a friend.</p>
            <p class="q"> I have a suggestion&shy;/feedback.</p>
